		<main id="main" class="site-main" role="main"><article id="post-493" class="post-493 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-raspberrypi"><header class="entry-header"><h1 class="entry-title">RaspberryPi freezing?</h1>	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-content">
		<p>If your raspberrypi is freezing or hanging (even if becomes responsive again), try changing out the USB power cable or the closest hub.</p>
<p>#themoreyouknow</p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	
	<footer class="entry-footer"><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="/blog/raspberrypi-freezing/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published" datetime="2013-03-31T16:32:44+00:00">March 31, 2013</time><time class="updated" datetime="2013-03-31T16:33:22+00:00">March 31, 2013</time></a></span><span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span><a class="url fn n" href="/blog/author/admin/">Jarrod</a></span></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="/blog/category/raspberrypi/" rel="category tag">raspberrypi</a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer --></article><!-- #post-## --><div id="comments" class="comments-area">

			<h2 class="comments-title">
			2 thoughts on &ldquo;RaspberryPi freezing?&rdquo;		</h2>

		
		<ol class="comment-list"><li id="comment-975" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent">
			<article id="div-comment-975" class="comment-body"><footer class="comment-meta"><div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt="" src="http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/945d10168a7817c64276c164a57fa8de?s=56&amp;r=r" srcset="http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/945d10168a7817c64276c164a57fa8de?s=112&amp;r=r 2x" class="avatar avatar-56 photo" height="56" width="56"><b class="fn"><a href="http://treyhunner.com" rel="external nofollow" class="url">Trey Hunner</a></b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="/blog/raspberrypi-freezing/#comment-975">
							<time datetime="2013-04-01T04:45:43+00:00">
								April 1, 2013 at 4:45 am							</time></a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta --><div class="comment-content">
					<p>I wouldn&rsquo;t have thought of this.  I&rsquo;ll have to try this next time mine freezes.</p>
<p>Do you know why the cable matters?  I&rsquo;d think a partially broken circuit in the cable could cause a freeze, but I wonder whether the cable length or material of the wire matter.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-login" href="/blog/wp-login.php?redirect_to=http%3A%2F%2Fjarrodoverson.com%2Fblog%2Fraspberrypi-freezing%2F">Log in to Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body --><ol class="children"><li id="comment-976" class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor odd alt depth-2">
			<article id="div-comment-976" class="comment-body"><footer class="comment-meta"><div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt="" src="http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/74be2e435d69a5827de7b5d33e7b343d?s=56&amp;r=r" srcset="http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/74be2e435d69a5827de7b5d33e7b343d?s=112&amp;r=r 2x" class="avatar avatar-56 photo" height="56" width="56"><b class="fn"><a href="" rel="external nofollow" class="url">Jarrod</a></b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="/blog/raspberrypi-freezing/#comment-976">
							<time datetime="2013-04-01T05:04:30+00:00">
								April 1, 2013 at 5:04 am							</time></a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta --><div class="comment-content">
					<p>I would guess the rpi&rsquo;s needs are more time-sensitive and demanding than a normal usb device, so cables that squeaked passed QA for lesser devices may not be up to par.</p>
<p>Random thoughts from someone not qualified to give them, though.</p>
